taten Island community of Huguenot is named after Daniel Perrin and other Huguenots who settled in the area during the late 17th century."]}]},{"name":"Ooare","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Hoar  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hoar","meanings":["Germanic.  See  <b>Roger</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":9,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":40,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Ooare De Parre was born in 1250, in Prescot, Lancashire, England as the son of Adam Prescott De Parre and Mrs. Jeanne De Parre. He had at least 1 son. He died about 1310, in his hometown, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1250–about 1310":"1250–umbes 1310","1250–1310":"1250–1310","1265–1303":"1265–1303","–1265":"–1265","1228–Female":"1228–Surnud","1228":"1228","1259":"1259","1303":"1303","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","about 1310":"umbes 1310","1250":"1250","about 1265":"umbes 1265","1290":"1290","Parr, Lancashire, England":"Parr, Lancashire, England","Prescot, Lancashire, England":"Prescot, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1250–about 1310":"1250–noin 1310","1250–1310":"1250–1310","1265–1303":"1265–1303","–1265":"–1265","1228–Female":"1228–Kuollut","1228":"1228","1259":"1259","1303":"1303","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","about 1310":"noin 1310","1250":"1250","about 1265":"noin 1265","1290":"1290","Parr, Lancashire, England":"Parr, Lancashire, England","Prescot, Lancashire, England":"Prescot, Lanc